{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 12:49:28.798552", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"router_dist_2_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dhcp_service_down\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional):\n- Restart and enable isc-dhcp-relay on router_dist_2_1 (systemctl restart --now isc-dhcp-relay; systemctl enable isc-dhcp-relay) and verify with journalctl for root cause of previous failure.\n- Confirm DHCPDISCOVER/Offer flow with tcpdump on br0 and between router_dist_2_1 and DHCP server (UDP 67/68).\n- Verify hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 obtain leases and become reachable; check DHCP server lease file for new leases in that pool.\n- If the relay repeatedly fails, capture logs (journalctl -u isc-dhcp-relay) and investigate config, resource limits, or package issues.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2343, "output_tokens": 192, "total_tokens": 2535, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
